			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Join Codecademy&#39;s growing design team and help create the best educational experience online.</p>
<p>
Have you ever contemplated how design can change the way people learn online? Are you passionate about user-centered design and have an avid appetite for interaction models, design systems, data visualization, and well-crafted digital experiences? Codecademy is seeking an exceptional designer with a proven track record for creating functional, elegant and impactful design solutions.</p>
<p>
As a product designer at Codecademy, you&#39;ll be involved in the product development process from start to finish. From brainstorming entirely new features to designing usable flows and beautiful interfaces, you&#39;ll exercise your full range of product, interaction, and visual design skills on a daily basis.</p>
<p>
You&#39;ll enjoy a high level of ownership of the features you work on. You&#39;ll partner with engineering, community, and data analysis to build and iterate on various design challenges in our product. We&#39;re looking for someone who sweats the details and is ready to tackle any design challenge that comes up between concepting and launching a product.</p>
<p>
Your work will empower millions of people worldwide to learn how to code and create something. Together, we can redesign education and create the best online learning experience.</p>
<p>
<strong>Role &amp; Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Work collaboratively with other designers, engineers, and product managers on multiple interrelated projects in a fast-paced environment.</li>
<li>
Evaluate data from multiple sources, synthesize it, and develop design strategies according to best UX practices.</li>
<li>
Take broad, conceptual ideas and turn them into congruent scenarios, usable flows, and simple, intuitive interfaces.</li>
<li>
Make high-level contributions to product strategy by identifying new opportunities, generating innovative solutions, creating emotionally engaging designs, and improving existing features.</li>
<li>
Be an advocate for an integrated, consistent UI throughout the product, and for a cohesive set of design principles and patterns.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Detail-oriented, self-motivated with a passion for pixel perfection, consistency, organization, usability, and discoverability.</li>
<li>
Excellent verbal communication skills and ability to soundly discuss design decisions.</li>
<li>
Strong visual communication skills with a keen eye for typography, layout, and color.</li>
<li>
Portfolio that showcases a proven record of delivering inventive solutions on time for demanding and complex design problems.</li>
<li>
Proficiency with the Adobe Suite.</li>
<li>
Understanding of how a design would be implemented in code (HTML, CSS, JavaScript).</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Experience</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
2 to 5 years of experience designing for web or mobile platforms.</li>
</ul>
<p>
-</p>
<p>
<strong>Sound like you? To apply, send a link to your portfolio with a brief introduction.</strong></p>
<p>
<em>A resume is NOT required; you can use a blank document.</em></p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
]]></description>
